First off, I love this idea.

Second of all, good job on remembering the italics for genus names and the like. There are some places where you shouldn't use italics - as a clade name, Dinosauria remains unitalicized; and if you're talking about a taxonomic group of animals (e.g. spinosaur) the name of it is generally unitalicized and lowercase as well. (A couple spelling mistakes regarding names as well - for example Archeopteryx I don't blame you though, I have a hard time wrapping my head around the Chinese language too.) There are a couple of other details that strike me as well, although I can't put my finger on it exactly. All this does seem a bit nitpicky, but paleontology is my thing so I can't help myself :P

Third, I must say the imagery of Therizinosaurus is quite delightful, especially in the context you've given it here.







